# Credentials for the WebSocket FEED only (logger phase, issue #13).
#
# REST order books stay public (no auth) on both venues. But the WebSocket
# feeds require an authenticated handshake even for public market data:
#   - Kalshi:        wss://external-api-ws.kalshi.com/orderbook_delta
#   - Polymarket US: wss://api.polymarket.us/v1/ws/markets
#
# READ-ONLY USE ONLY. These keys are full-access, so the safety rule is enforced
# in code: the feed modules never import or call any order-placing surface
# (`orders.*`). Never place an order from collection code.
#
# Never commit a real .env (it is gitignored, as is *.pem). The PM US secret key
# is shown ONCE at generation time — back it up in a secret manager immediately;
# it cannot be retrieved again.

# --- Kalshi (RSA key pair) ---
# KALSHI_API_KEY_ID is the key UUID; the private key is a downloaded PEM file.
# Point KALSHI_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH at that .pem (kept out of git by the *.pem rule).
KALSHI_API_KEY_ID=
KALSHI_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=

# --- Polymarket US (access key + secret) ---
POLYMARKET_KEY_ID=
POLYMARKET_SECRET_KEY=
